title: Week 7: Brevard high school football
text:
Week 7: Brevard high school football Brian McCallum , FLORIDA TODAY 4:40 p.m. EDT October 8, 2015 Rockledge QB Jaquez Lyons tries to fend off the tackle of Space Coast player Jared Spinner (37) during last Friday’s game at McLarty Stadium. (Photo: Craig Bailey/FLORIDA TODAY) 
Astronaut (3-2) at Rockledge (2-3) 
7 p.m., McLarty Stadium 
Last week: The War Eagles came from behind to defeat Orlando Jones, 15-14. Rockledge fell to Space Coast, 29-28 in OT. 
Game note: Astronaut leads the series with Rockledge, 27-13, winning last year, 12-3. Rockledge last won in 2012, 23-21 in Titusville. 
Melbourne (0-5) at Heritage (4-1) 
7 
Last week: The Bulldogs lost to Viera, 49-3, while the Panthers beat Okeechobee, 41-14. 
Game note: These teams haven’t played since 2012, when Melbourne won in Palm Bay, 39-6. In 2011, the only other meeting, Melbourne won at home, 39-7. 
Palm Bay (4-1) at Viera (3-3) 
7:30 
Last week: The Pirates won at Titusville, 45-10. The Hawks won at Melbourne, 49-3. 
Game note: Third meeting between the two football programs. Palm Bay won in 2010, 47-7 at Viera. The year before, it won at home, 38-0. 
Cocoa Beach (1-5) at Eau Gallie (3-2) 
7 
Last week: The Minutemen lost to MCC, 47-8. On Thursday, the Commodores beat Bayside, 45-0. 
Game note: Cocoa Beach leads the series, 10-8. Eau Gallie won last year, 48-0 at Cocoa Beach. 
Sebastian River (3-1, 2-0) at Bayside (0-5, 0-2) 
7 
Last week: The Sharks defeated Jensen Beach, 31-14. The Bears lost a Thursday game at Eau Gallie, 45-0. 
Game note: District 14-6A game. Sebastian River has won three in a row since a season-opening 10-9 home loss to Titusville. 
Lakeland Christian (6-0) at Melbourne CC (4-2) 
7 
Last week: The Vikings beat Land O’Lakes, 27-14. The Hustlers won at Cocoa Beach, 47-8. 
Game note: Lakeland Christian, ranked No. 2 in Class 3A, eliminated MCC from the playoffs last year in Lakeland, 32-26, and reached the state semifinals. 
Agape Christian (1-4) at Holy Trinity (4-1) 
7 
Last week: The Saints lost at Victory Christian, 41-6. The Tigers won at Deltona Trinity Christian, 34-19. 
Game note: Holy Trinity opened the 2014 season with a 24-6 win at Agape Christian. When the two played in 2013 in Melbourne, the Tigers won, 30-0. 
Space Coast (3-1) at Poinciana (0-6) 
7 
Last week: The Vipers made a 2-point conversion in OT for a 29-28 win at Rockledge. The Eagles lost at Eustis, 61-0. 
Game note: This makeup game was originally scheduled for Sept. 25 but was postponed due to lightning. Poinciana has been shut out three times, with a combined margin of 186-0. 
Merritt Island Christian (3-2) at International Community (3-1) 
7, Winter Park 
Last week: The Cougars defeated Landmark Christian on Monday, 51-8. The Comets won at Master’s Academy of Oviedo, 45-6. 
Game note: The teams have three common opponents, which MIC has beaten by a combined 92-61 score, while International Community has a 92-38 margin.
